// --- SLIDE: The Vision ---
#slide(title: "Context")[
  #set align(center)
  #text(size: 1.1em)[*Objective*: Study Information Diffusion on a Microblogging Social Media.]

  #set align(left)
  #v(0.5em)
  
  *Definition*: Information diffusion is the study of how discrete pieces of content (called from now on posts) propagate through a network infrastructure over time.
  
  When posts propagate, they form *cascades*, trees consisting of the users that see and interact with the post. Therefore,

  #v(0.3em)
  #set align(center)
  #text(size: 1.1em)[_Information Diffusion_ is the study of _Cascades_ generated by _Posts propagation_.]

]

