#slide(title: "(1) - AT Protocol")[
  Bluesky is a decentralized microblogging platform --- a twitter clone, but built in an open specification, the Authenticated Transfer Protocol, *ATProto*.

  #v(0.7em)
  The ATP decouples data from the application, splitting the view (AppView) from the data --- the *Firehose*.

  #v(0.7em)
  It's easy to listen to all events from the firehose: post creations, reposts, likes, follows, unfollows, blocks...
]


#slide(title: "(1) - Problem Scope")[
  #v(0.2em)
  We model a microblogging social media platform under these simplifying assumptions:

  #v(0.3em)
      - *Just the Following Feed:* reverse-chronological timelines (no recommenders)
      - *Static Users and Followers:* no new users nor follows while the simulation runs.
      - *No Mutes nor Blocks:* following a user means receiving all their posts
      - *No Quotes, no Replies:* only likes and reposts
      - *No User Profiles:* users are limited to their timeline, no browsing other profiles

  #v(0.4em)
  #set align(center)
  #text(size: 1.3em)[A user can only do two things with a post: \ either *like* or *repost*, or just ignore it.]

]

#slide(title: "(1) - Model Intuition")[

  Given a user $u in cal(U)$, it has a timeline $cal(T)_t (u)$ filled with posts $i in cal(I)$. 

  Main idea: user is online, they are *scrolling* through their timelines, and they can interact with a post with a *like* or a *repost*, or just *ignore* it and keep scrolling.

  When $u$ reposts $i$, $i$ *propagates* to the followers of $u$, $cal(N)_"out" (u)$:

  $ "for" v "in" cal(N)_"out" (u): "push"(cal(T)_t (v), i) $

  But $v in cal(N)_"out" (u)$ will not immediately see reposted content $i$ if it has been scrolling for a while, as the user sees _past_ content, so it gets enqueued in $cal(T)_t (v)$.

  When $v$ connects online again and starts scrolling, will eventually see $i$ if the time $v$ has been online is not too long: then $i$ will never have the change to propagate. 

  Also, if a user does not have any new posts to see $cal(T)_t (u) = emptyset$ then will disconnect and connect later.
]

