#slide(title: "(1) - Continuous-Time Independent Cascade")[
  #v(0.3em)
  #text(size: 0.9em, weight: "bold")[*Definition.*] The CTIC model preserves independent transmission across edges but replaces fixed step-based probabilities with a time-dependent transmission likelihood. Each edge has a pairwise transmission rate $alpha_(j,i)$ 
  #v(0.5em)
  #set align(center)
  Once user $u$ propagated a post $i$ at $t_u$ ---assuming $v$ will also propagate it---, follower $v$ will repost $v$ at some latter time $t_v > t_u$ assu
  #v(2em)

